Open System Interconnection:

Application Layer: used by web/Network Applications. protocols: http, http/s, tcp, smtp, telnet
Presentation Layer: Translation, Compression and Encryption, Decryption of the data.
Session Layer: Session Management, Authorization, Authentication.
Transport Layer: Reliability of communication, Segmentation (seq n.o, port n.o to packets), flow control (Regulate amount of data
                  transmission), Error control (checksum to packets to avoid data loss). Protocols: TCP (connection), UDP (connectionless)
Network Layer: Logical addressing (assign I.P address to packets), Path determination, Routing
Data Link Layer: Data is framed.
Physical Layer: Converts the binaries from D.L.L to signals.
